      <head>Verein der Musiklehrerinnen</head>

      <div>
        <p>Viennese professional body founded at the instigation of Rosa Lutz in 1886 or 1888, its
          leader for thirty-five years from 1893 being <ref cRef="entity-000796">Marie
            Schneider-Grünzweig</ref>. The Association allied itself with the Bund
          Österreichischer Frauenvereine [Federation of Austrian Women's Associations] in
          1915, and in 1935 with the Klub der Wiener Musikerinnen [Club of Viennese Female
          Musicians].</p>

        
        <p>The Association's motto was: "Musik ist eine höhere Offenbarung als Weisheit und
        Philosophie" [Music is a higher form of revelation than wisdom and philosophy] (Beethoven)</p>
      </div>
